  "narrative" : "The chair dissolves into molecules, atoms, fields, interactions, and at no point do you arrive at the thing itself. Four traditions pressed on the idea of a self-subsistent object from different directions and found the same dissolution: Whitehead from process metaphysics, Kant from epistemology, Rovelli from relational quantum mechanics, Wittgenstein from the logic of language. The event is primary; the object is derivative.",
